TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a= random(-10, 10);
$a1 = random(2, 10);
$a2 = random(2, 10);
$a3 = random(1, 10);
$b1 = random(1,3,.5);
$b = $a+$b1;
$c = $b+$b1;
$d = $c+$b1;

BEGIN_TEXT
Let \( \displaystyle \int_{$a}^{$d} f(x)\, dx =$a1, \ \int_{$a}^{$b} f(x)\, dx=$a2, \ \int_{$c}^{$d} f(x)\, dx =$a3 \). 
$BR$BR
By using the rules for combining integrals with adjacent intervals, find$BR \( \displaystyle \int_{$b}^{$c} f(x)\, dx= \) \{ans_rule( 20)\} 
$PAR$PAR
Use linearity, the rules for definite integrals, and the formula for the definite integral of a constant function to compute$BR \( \displaystyle \int_{$c}^{$b} \big($a1 f(x)- $a2\big) \, dx= \) \{ans_rule( 20)\}

END_TEXT

$ans1="$a1-($a2)-($a3)";
$ans2="-($a1*($ans1))+$a2*$b1";

ANS(num_cmp($ans1), num_cmp($ans2));

